feat: initial proof of concept - FluidLM 

Transformer-free language model replacing O(N²) self-attention
with reaction-diffusion PDEs. Linear complexity, no KV-cache.

Core components:
- FluidLayer: multi-scale dilated diffusion (d=1,4,16) + reaction MLP + memory pump
- FluidNet: 4-layer stack with weight-tied head (~36M params)
- Adaptive compute: Turing equilibrium early stopping (eval mode)
- Real-time Streamlit dashboard with live hyperparameter control
- Adaptive compute validation experiment (eval_adaptive.py)

Fixes in the current version:
- Relative turbulence metric (scale-invariant convergence detection)
- Corrected diffusion regularization (penalizes anti-diffusion coefficients)
- Differential LR per dilation group (prevents long-range coeff collapse)

Status: proof of concept - trains and converges, linear scaling verified,
adaptive mechanism implemented but not yet statistically validated.